<h1>Reptile Shop Management System</h1>
<p>Full Stack • MongoDB • Admin Dashboard • Real Client Project</p>
</div>

<div class="container">

<!-- 🔥 OVERVIEW -->
<div class="box">
<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>
This project is a fully dynamic, full-stack reptile shop management system developed for a real client. The application enables a business owner to control their entire website through a centralized admin dashboard, eliminating the need for manual updates or ongoing developer support.
</p>

<p>
The system manages inventory, product presentation, pricing, availability, and customer interaction through a MongoDB-driven backend. Each product (animal) is stored as structured data and rendered dynamically using EJS templates, allowing real-time updates across the entire site.
</p>

<p>
When a new animal is added through the admin dashboard, the system automatically generates a new product page. This demonstrates a scalable, data-driven architecture where the frontend adapts based on database content rather than static code.
</p>

<p>
This project represents a complete end-to-end development lifecycle, from initial planning and design to deployment and real-world usage.
</p>

</div>

<!-- 🔥 SKILL SET -->
<div class="box">
<h2>Skill Set & Real-World Application</h2>

<p>
This project demonstrates a complete full-stack development skill set applied within a real business environment.
</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Full-Stack Development:</strong> Designed and built both frontend and backend systems using Node.js, Express, EJS, and MongoDB.</li>

<li><strong>Database Architecture:</strong> Structured MongoDB schemas to support scalable inventory systems and real-time updates.</li>

<li><strong>Dynamic Web Systems:</strong> Built a data-driven architecture where pages are automatically generated from database content.</li>

<li><strong>Admin Dashboard Development:</strong> Created a system allowing non-technical users to manage content, inventory, and site functionality.</li>

<li><strong>UI/UX Design:</strong> Designed layouts and interactions based on real client needs and usability.</li>

<li><strong>Deployment & Production:</strong> Took the system from development into a working production environment.</li>

<li><strong>Marketing & Advertising:</strong> Promoted the website using Google Ads, generating traffic and visibility.</li>

<li><strong>Client Collaboration:</strong> Worked directly with a business owner to define requirements, iterate features, and deliver a final product.</li>
</ul>

<p>
These skills are applicable to any business requiring scalable web systems, inventory management, or automated content control.
</p>

</div>

<!-- 🔥 DEVELOPMENT CONTEXT -->
<div class="box">
<h2>Project Context & Development Process</h2>

<p>
This project was developed as a real-world business solution, beginning with direct communication with the client to understand their operational needs. The goal was to create a system that would allow full control over inventory and website content without requiring ongoing technical support.
</p>

<p>
The system was designed and built using a full-stack architecture where the backend handles data, routing, and logic, while the frontend dynamically renders content. This approach ensures that the website can scale and evolve without structural changes to the codebase.
</p>

<p>
Throughout development, the project followed an iterative process. Features were refined and adjusted based on real feedback from the client, ensuring the final product aligned with actual business use rather than assumptions.
</p>

<p>
After development, the project was deployed and promoted using Google Ads, demonstrating real-world application beyond coding. This included exposure to user traffic, performance considerations, and customer interaction.
</p>

<p>
This project demonstrates the ability to take a concept from idea to production, combining technical execution with real-world business understanding.
</p>

</div>

<!-- 🔥 COLLABORATION + GITHUB -->
<div class="box">
<h2>Development Workflow & Collaboration</h2>

<p>
The project was managed using Git and GitHub for version control, allowing structured development, organized updates, and reliable code management.
</p>

<p>
Development involved direct collaboration with the client, including requirement gathering, feature planning, and iterative improvements. This ensured that the final system matched real business needs and user expectations.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Version control using Git and GitHub</li>
<li>Iterative feature development based on feedback</li>
<li>Direct client communication and requirement gathering</li>
<li>Real-world problem solving and system adaptation</li>
<li>Deployment and post-development support</li>
</ul>

<p>
This reflects experience working in real-world development environments, where communication, adaptability, and delivery are just as important as coding.
</p>

</div>

